2. Definitions

"Licensor" means 株式会社DENCYU.

"Software" means the LayerDraw source code, object code, binaries, packages,
and other materials that expressly identify this License or are assigned this
License by the repository's authoritative licensing matrix. Software does not
include material expressly licensed under another license.

"You" means the individual or legal entity exercising rights under this
License.

"Your Organization" means You and any legal entity that controls, is controlled
by, or is under common control with You. "Control" means the power to direct
management or policies, whether by ownership, contract, or otherwise.

"End User" means a third party that accesses or uses a product or service made
available by You. Your personnel and contractors acting solely to operate Your
product or service are not End Users.

"Schema Definition" means an EntityType, RelationType, Column, Constraint,
Layer, or an equivalent definition that determines the kinds, structure,
allowed relationships, or semantic rules of data managed by the Software.

"General-Purpose Schema Authoring" means a capability by which an End User can,
directly or indirectly, create, modify, delete, import, install, generate, or
cause arbitrary Schema Definitions. It includes equivalent capabilities
provided through a user interface, API, SDK, MCP tool, AI agent, uploaded file,
Pack, Template, service account, or operator automation. It also includes a
capability that encodes types, fields, relationships, constraints, or semantic
rules as graph instances, relations, rows, values, or other data when the
practical effect is to let an End User define an arbitrary schema or type
system, regardless of the internal representation or operation name. Asking the
provider to perform genuinely bespoke professional services that result in a
provider-controlled fixed model is not, by itself, General-Purpose Schema
Authoring.

"Fixed Model Application" means a product or service in which:

  a. You or Your personnel determine and control all Schema Definitions;
  b. End Users do not receive General-Purpose Schema Authoring;
  c. End Users may create, modify, query, view, render, export, or collaborate on
     graph instances, relations, rows, values, queries, views, layouts, assets,
     or other data within the provider-defined model; and
  d. the product or service is presented and operated as a domain application,
     workflow, analysis product, AI product, or other provider-defined solution,
     rather than as a general-purpose LayerDraw, diagram, graph, or semantic
     layer authoring service.

A Fixed Model Application may be commercial, paid, free of charge,
multi-tenant, or operated for multiple customers. It may offer a catalog of
provider-defined models. Bounded configuration that does not create or modify a
Schema Definition does not prevent an application from being a Fixed Model
Application.

"Customer-Controlled Deployment" means a deployment used for the customer's
own internal purposes and operated primarily in an account, environment, or
infrastructure controlled by that customer. Installation, support, maintenance,
and remote operation by a contractor do not change that status when the
contractor is not offering the deployment as a shared or general-purpose hosted
LayerDraw service.

"Read-Only Viewing Service" means a hosted product or service that:

  a. receives or stores user-selected LayerDraw projects or content solely to
     view, embed, render, download, or export them;
  b. may provide authentication, access control, and share links only as needed
     for those read-only purposes;
  c. does not let an End User create or modify Schema Definitions, graph
     instances, relations, rows, values, queries, views, layouts, or assets; and
  d. does not provide collaboration, revision history, Registry or Pack
     management, general-purpose workspace or project management, or
     general-purpose SDK, API, or MCP access.

"Restricted Hosted Offering" means a hosted or managed product or service for
third parties that does any of the following:

  a. provides General-Purpose Schema Authoring;
  b. provides access to a substantial set of LayerDraw's general-purpose editor,
     project, server, SDK, API, MCP, registry, collaboration, or authoring
     functionality as a product or service in itself;
  c. offers stock, substantially stock, white-labeled, or rebranded LayerDraw;
  d. markets or operates a LayerDraw-compatible cloud, general-purpose semantic
     layer builder, general-purpose graph authoring service, or equivalent
     substitute for LayerDraw; or
  e. uses an intermediary, service account, AI agent, import flow, Pack,
     Template, or operator automation to provide an End User with the practical
     equivalent of any capability described above.

An offering is not a Restricted Hosted Offering merely because it is
commercial, paid, multi-tenant, uses the Software on a server, competes with a
particular LayerDraw use case, is a Fixed Model Application, or is a Read-Only
Viewing Service.

"Commercial License" means a separate written agreement with the Licensor that
expressly authorizes use otherwise restricted by this License.

